East London police seized tik with a street value of R14080 at the weekend.Warrant Officer Hazel Mqala said a suspect was arrested in possession of the crystal meth in a stop and search operation carried out by the crime prevention unit in the city’s CBD on Sunday. Also in East London, a shebeen operating without a licence was closed down in Duncan Village. Liquor and dangerous weapons, including a firearm and knives, were confiscated. “For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions”.